                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">Fol. iiiv(erso)</locus><desc>A small painting of a face</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004">Fol. ivr(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1114Gabriel"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1114Gabriel</span></ref>, with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> drawn (giving help against the Italians?); rifle and (Italian?) soldier pictured below.
                    Captions (in black ink) <q>“Gabriel, Announcer of Gladness,” “I beseech you”</q> (in pencil) <q>, “Gabriel, Announcer of Gladness” “sword” “Gabriel” “Mauser” (type of rifle)</q> (in red ink) <q>“Gabriel, Announcer of Gladness”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#vr(ecto)" facs="005">Fol. vr(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> Crude drawing in pink ink with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> drawn. Caption <q>“Ṭǝqǝmt 4, 1917”</q></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                      Decorative designs:
